        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Data Agents in LlamaIndex"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Data agents",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " are LLM-powered reasoning loops that decide which tools to call, observe the results, and iterate until they produce a final answer. Unlike a query engine \u2014 which retrieves and synthesises in one shot \u2014 an agent can issue multiple tool calls, use results from one call to inform the next, and handle tasks that require multi-step reasoning."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LlamaIndex agents are built on two reasoning strategies: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ReAct",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (Reasoning + Acting), which alternates between Thought/Action/Observation steps using plain text, and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "OpenAI function calling",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", which uses the model's native structured tool-call API."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "LlamaIndex data agent reasoning loop diagram"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Creating a ReActAgent"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The simplest agent wraps one or more tools and uses the ReAct reasoning strategy."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from llama_index.core.agent import ReActAgent\nfrom llama_index.core.tools import FunctionTool\nfrom llama_index.llms.openai import OpenAI\n\ndef multiply(a: float, b: float) -> float:\n    \"\"\"Multiply two numbers and return the result.\"\"\"\n    return a * b\n\ndef add(a: float, b: float) -> float:\n    \"\"\"Add two numbers and return the result.\"\"\"\n    return a + b\n\ntools = [\n    FunctionTool.from_defaults(fn=multiply),\n    FunctionTool.from_defaults(fn=add),\n]\n\nllm = OpenAI(model=\"gpt-4o-mini\")\nagent = ReActAgent.from_tools(tools, llm=llm, verbose=True)\n\nresponse = agent.chat(\"What is (12.3 * 7) + 42?\")\nprint(response)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "With "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "verbose=True",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", each Thought/Action/Observation step is printed. This is invaluable for debugging, because you can see exactly which tools the model called and what it concluded from their results."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "QueryEngineTool: Giving Agents Access to Knowledge Bases"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Wrapping a query engine as a tool gives the agent access to a vector index. The agent decides when to query it \u2014 useful when the agent needs to combine retrieved facts with other tools."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from llama_index.core import VectorStoreIndex, SimpleDirectoryReader\nfrom llama_index.core.tools import QueryEngineTool\nfrom llama_index.core.agent import ReActAgent\nfrom llama_index.llms.openai import OpenAI\n\n# Build the index\ndocuments = SimpleDirectoryReader(\"./docs\").load_data()\nindex = VectorStoreIndex.from_documents(documents)\nquery_engine = index.as_query_engine()\n\n# Wrap as a tool\nknowledge_tool = QueryEngineTool.from_defaults(\n    query_engine=query_engine,\n    name=\"company_docs\",\n    description=(\n        \"Use this tool to answer questions about the company's internal documentation. \"\n        \"Input should be a question in natural language.\"\n    ),\n)\n\nagent = ReActAgent.from_tools(\n    [knowledge_tool],\n    llm=OpenAI(model=\"gpt-4o\"),\n    verbose=True,\n)\n\nresponse = agent.chat(\"What are the company's engineering onboarding steps?\")\nprint(response)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Multiple Tools and Multi-Step Reasoning"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The ReAct agent naturally handles tasks that require combining knowledge retrieval with computation or external API calls."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import httpx\nfrom llama_index.core.tools import FunctionTool, QueryEngineTool\nfrom llama_index.core.agent import ReActAgent\nfrom llama_index.llms.openai import OpenAI\n\ndef get_current_date() -> str:\n    \"\"\"Return today's date in YYYY-MM-DD format.\"\"\"\n    from datetime import date\n    return str(date.today())\n\ndef search_web(query: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Search the web for recent news. Returns a short summary.\"\"\"\n    # Placeholder \u2014 integrate a real search API in production\n    return f\"[Web search result for: {query}]\"\n\ntools = [\n    FunctionTool.from_defaults(fn=get_current_date),\n    FunctionTool.from_defaults(fn=search_web),\n    knowledge_tool,   # from the previous example\n]\n\nagent = ReActAgent.from_tools(tools, llm=OpenAI(model=\"gpt-4o\"), verbose=True)\n\nresponse = agent.chat(\n    \"What day is it today, and what are the latest AI developments from the docs?\"\n)\nprint(response)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "OpenAI Agent (Function Calling)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Use "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "OpenAIAgent",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " when your target model supports native function calling (gpt-4o, gpt-4-turbo). It is more reliable than ReAct for tool selection because the model is explicitly trained on function-call JSON."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from llama_index.core.agent import OpenAIAgent\nfrom llama_index.llms.openai import OpenAI\n\nagent = OpenAIAgent.from_tools(\n    tools,\n    llm=OpenAI(model=\"gpt-4o\"),\n    verbose=True,\n)\n\nresponse = agent.chat(\"Calculate (25 * 4) and then look up company policy on remote work.\")\nprint(response)\nprint(response.sources)   # list of tool calls and their results\n"
          }
        ]
      },
